Time Limit: 1 sec
Memory: 256 MB

Description
Consider a competition that uses a point system to determine the team rankings.

After a match:

* The winning team receives 3 points
* The losing team receives 0 points
* If tied, both teams receive 1 point

The team that accumulates the most points wins the competition.

However, if there is a tie, the team with the highest goal difference among the tied teams is the winner.

Score is calculated as:

score = 3 × wins + draws

Goal difference is calculated as:

goal difference = scored − conceded

Note: If the score and goal difference are the same, return the team with the lowest index.

You are given 4 arrays of the same length: wins, draws, scored, and conceded.

Within each array, the ith element represents the corresponding metric for the ith team – i.e.:

* Scored goals: scored[i]
* Conceded goals: conceded[i]
* Matches won: wins[i]
* Matches tied: draws[i]

(for each i in 0,1,…,wins.length - 1).

Determine the indices of the winning team and the team in second place.

Return an array of exactly two integers:

* The first is the index of the winning team
* The second is the index of the team in second place

Input Format
The first line contains a single integer T - the number of test cases.

For each test case:

The first line contains an integer n - the number of teams.

The second line contains n space separated integers representing wins.

The third line contains n space separated integers representing draws.

The fourth line contains n space separated integers representing scored goals.

The fifth line contains n space separated integers representing conceded goals.

Output Format
For each test case, output an array of two integers – the index of the winning team followed by the index of the team in second place.

Constraints
1 ≤ T ≤ 100
2 ≤ n ≤ 100
0 ≤ wins[i], draws[i] ≤ 100
0 ≤ scored[i], conceded[i] ≤ 1000

Sample Input 1
1
3
2 1 0
1 5 6
20 15 10
20 10 15

Sample Output 1
1 0

Sample Input 2
1
4
3 1 2 2
1 5 4 4
30 10 20 40
32 13 18 37

Sample Output 2
3 2

Note

Sample Input 1:

The team with index 0 received 2 × 3 + 1 = 7 points.
The team with index 1 received 1 × 3 + 5 = 8 points.
The team with index 2 received 0 × 3 + 6 = 6 points.

Since 8 > 7 > 6, the team with index 1 is the winner, and the team with index 0 is in second place.

Thus, the answer is [1, 0].

Sample Input 2:

The team with index 0 received 3 × 3 + 1 = 10 points.
The team with index 3 received 2 × 3 + 4 = 10 points.

Three teams are tied with the highest number of points: teams with indices 0, 2, and 3.

The team with index 0 has a goal difference of 30 − 32 = −2.
The team with index 2 has a goal difference of 20 − 18 = 2.
The team with index 3 has a goal difference of 40 − 37 = 3.

Since 3 > 2 > −2, the team with index 3 is the winner, and the team with index 2 is in second place.

So, the answer is [3, 2].



#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
typedef long long ll;
#define endl "\n"   // optional, better to avoid redefining endl


bool comp(const pair<pair<int,int>,int> a ,pair<pair<int,int>,int> b)
{
    if(a.first.first != b.first.first)
    {
        return a.first.first > b.first.first;
    }

    if(a.first.second != b.first.second)
    {
        return a.first.second > b.first.second;
    }

    return a.second < b.second;


}
void solve() {
    int n;
    cin>>n;
    vector<int>scored(n);
    vector<int>conceded(n);
    vector<int>win(n);
    vector<int>draw(n);

    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++)
    {
        cin>>win[i];
    }
    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++)
    {
        cin>>draw[i];
    }
    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++)
    {
        cin>>scored[i];
    }
    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++)
    {
        cin>>conceded[i];
    }
    vector<int>score(n);
    vector<int>goaldiff(n);

    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++)
    {
        score[i] = 3 * win[i] + draw[i];
        goaldiff[i] = scored[i] - conceded[i];
    }
    vector<pair<pair<int,int>, int>> teams;
    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++)
    {
        teams.push_back({{score[i],goaldiff[i]}, i});
    }

    sort(teams.begin(),teams.end(),comp);

    cout<<teams[0].second<<" "<<teams[1].second<<endl;
}

int main() {
    ios::sync_with_stdio(false);
    cin.tie(nullptr);

    int t;
    cin >> t;
    while (t--) {
        solve();
    }

    return 0;
}
